            <title>[HBASE-3603] Remove  -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError  autodump of heap option on OOME</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3603</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By default the  -XX:+HeapDumpOnOutOfMemoryError  option is set for HBase.  Means we&apos;ll dump heap when we OOME.  In the heaps we run with 8G, 16G, etc., these can make for hefty files.  No one really looks at these things other than a few weirdos and even then, the interesting ones are too big to ship easily.  Meantime, they can cause headache.  E.g. you are on EC2, root is but a small partition, and you set up hbase on root partition... a heap dump could cause your root partition to fill and make the machine unapproachable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
